        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 5:31PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles south of Greenville Downtown, or 7 miles southwest of
Simpsonville, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Princeton, Fork Shoals, and Hickory Tavern.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
